        <div class="slide active">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Selection Sort

            A simple comparison-based sorting algorithm.

            - Repeatedly selects the smallest element
            - Places it in its correct position
            - Divides the array into **sorted** and **unsorted** parts
            </script>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="slide active">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Core Idea

            At each step:

            1. Find the minimum element in the unsorted portion
            2. Swap it with the first unsorted element
            3. Expand the sorted portion by one element

            Sorted | Unsorted  
            :---:|:---:
            </script>


          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="slide active">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Step-by-Step Example

            Sort the array:

            [64, 25, 12, 22, 11]

            **Pass 1**
            - Minimum = 11
            - Swap with 64

            Result:
            [11, 25, 12, 22, 64]
            </script>


          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="slide active">
          <div class="slide-content markdown">
            <script type="text/markdown">
            # Visual Representation

            mermaid
            graph LR;
